<br>
*cough*, ok now for reals.........If I die and there's no cleric around, I leave an arrow or something on there in case I run into a buddy later.  I'd rather at least have a chance of getting a rez later than to simply eat the exp loss.  I've lined up two or three corpses in one area with the hopes that maybe some nice cleric will help me out later.  If not, oh well, I'm not any worse off.  Hell, I'll take a 10% rez.  Better than nothin'.  And I always say thank you and offer to pay even if they tell me not to.  Sometimes, it's just the gesture of the offer that's important. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#E9D756>- </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr>Erollisi Marr, The Queen of Love</a><font color=#E9D756> - </font><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames</a> <font color=#E9D756> - </font> <br>
